===============================================================================
  AUTOKEYS / AUTODUMP — silent prod.keys refresh via hekate ↔ Lockpick_RCM
===============================================================================

Port of the 4IFIR auto-refresh mechanism for prod.keys. When HOS is updated on
SysMMC or EmuMMC, hekate detects the change at boot and silently chainloads a
Lockpick_RCM variant that dumps keys and returns control to hekate via
bootloader/update.bin. No user interaction, no perceivable boot delay.

Applies to:
  * hekate fork (any recent CTCaer-based)
  * Lockpick_RCM fork (shchmue-based)

Design (split brain):
  - hekate side does NO crypto. It only reads the 14-byte pkg1 timestamp +
    1-byte master-key revision from BOOT0 (plaintext header — Mariko skips the
    0x170-byte bl_hdr_t210b01_t prefix first, Erista starts at 0). Compares
    against bootloader/sys/autokeys.bin. If stale, writes
    bootloader/sys/autokeys.request and dispatches bootloader/sys/lockpick.bin.

  - Lockpick side ships a silent dispatcher that runs before the main menu.
    If the request marker exists, it calls a new dump_keys_silent() wrapper
    (mutes gfx, skips btn_wait), then launches bootloader/update.bin to chain
    back to hekate. Lockpick's normal UI still works when invoked manually.

Tested: Mariko T210B01, HOS 20.x, shipped in 4IFIR 2026-04-19.
Erista expected to work (Lockpick-side TSEC flow is unchanged), not on-device
tested in this build.

SD layout the mechanism uses:
  bootloader/sys/autokeys.bin      — 36-byte state: magic 'AK4I', ts+mkey per NAND
  bootloader/sys/autokeys.request  — 36-byte request: magic 'AKRQ', retry counter
  bootloader/sys/autokeys.disable  — user opt-out marker (any content)
  bootloader/sys/autokeys.force    — user debug marker, forces redump
  bootloader/sys/autokeys.failed   — after 3 failed retries, stops re-triggering
  bootloader/sys/autokeys.log      — diagnostic log (gated by AK_DEBUG_LOG=1)
  bootloader/sys/lockpick.bin      — silent-aware Lockpick binary

Safety rails:
  - Pre-flight f_stat on lockpick.bin before writing the request (no-file → no-cycle)
  - Retry counter capped at 3; Lockpick increments on entry, hekate gives up at cap
  - hekate's _launch_payload had to lose its `static` qualifier (exposed for autokeys)
  - Lockpick's _derive_keys is called as-is — no changes to the crypto path

Payload size delta (example, Mariko T210B01):
  hekate:    +1,556 B compressed   (120,358 / 126,296 limit)
  Lockpick:  -577  B compressed    (109,787 / 126,296 limit — we saved by not
                                     renaming title.keys)

WARNING: the hekate patch removes `static` from _launch_payload so autokeys.c
can invoke it. If your fork has a different main.c layout, just re-expose
whatever payload-launch helper you already have.

